PulseOS – IR Tools Fix Update

This update focuses on stabilizing and repairing the IR Tools system. After extensive debugging and testing on the M5StickS3 hardware, IR learning and transmission are now functioning reliably.

Changes:
-Rebuilt IR Tools learning system to use NEC protocol decoding instead of raw waveform replay
-Added NEC address + command decoding during the learning process
-Implemented clean NEC frame generation for transmission
-Fixed issue where learned signals would store but fail to transmit properly
-Confirmed IR TX functionality using the built-in IR LED on pin 46
-Added persistent storage of learned NEC commands per profile and button
-Improved IR learning feedback messages and UI status indicators
-IR Tools now reliably learns and sends compatible remote commands

Notes:
-Current learning mode supports NEC protocol devices
-Some remotes may require multiple learning attempts due to timing variation
-Additional IR protocols will be added in future updates
